---
alwaysApply: true
---

Use FF Orbit MCP first-class commands before low-level patching.

Core behavior:
1) Resolve scope with the smallest read command (`pages.list`, `page.get`, `widgets.list`, `textfields.list`, `widget.get`).
2) Execute targeted first-class command (`page.*`, `widget.*`, `routes.*`, `widgets.updateMany`, etc.).
3) For writes, use changeset safety flow (`preview -> validate -> apply`) unless command already encapsulates it.
4) Report exact status (`applied` true/false), reasons, and concrete next step.

Guardrails:
- Do not assume page/widget IDs from names unless resolved first.
- Reuse prior selection/context for follow-up prompts ("this/that/it").
- Do not claim success unless `applyResult.applied === true` (or command-level `applied === true`).
- Avoid exploratory loops (`api.capabilities`, `schema.*`) for routine tasks.
